\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {A.2}{\ignorespaces Network evaluations per recovered span. The gradient-guided samplers spend a backward pass at every step, doubled when the Metropolis--Hastings correction is enabled, whereas the gradient-free baselines spend none. The single-pass rescoring method, which was the strongest baseline of Section~\ref {sec:results-baselines}, costs a small constant number of forward passes and no backward pass at all.}}{89}{table.caption.28}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:cost}{{A.2}{89}{Network evaluations per recovered span. The gradient-guided samplers spend a backward pass at every step, doubled when the Metropolis--Hastings correction is enabled, whereas the gradient-free baselines spend none. The single-pass rescoring method, which was the strongest baseline of Section~\ref {sec:results-baselines}, costs a small constant number of forward passes and no backward pass at all}{table.caption.28}{}}
